Senator Moses Kajwang’ will table a motion at the Senate calling for the investigation into last Tuesday’s assault on journalists at the Homa Bay county assembly. Standard Group journalist James Omoro was attacked and his camera smashed. Ramogi FM reporter Aly Abich was also assaulted. The two faced the wrath of police officers deployed to maintain law and order when the assembly resumed from recess. Kajwang’ said his motion will ensure IPOA is involved in the investigations and the journalists are compensated. Click here for the latest political news